Refunds by law: In Australia, consumers have a legal right to obtain a refund from a business for goods purchased if the goods are faulty, not fit for purpose or don't match description. More information at Seabourne Networks will accept returns and exchanges up to 30 days after delivery of products (software, licensing, extended support warranties excluded). If you are not satisfied with your purchase or if you received a damaged, defective, or a wrong item and need to replace it with the same item, please contact us for further information and instructions on how to return the product and how you'll receive a replacement. If you return an item for refund, the type of refund and how your refund is issued may differ based on the condition of the item, and how the item was purchased. Ultimately, to receive a full refund of the sale price, items must be in new condition and include all original packaging and accessories.
